.TH "TEMPORAL.NOW.INSTANT" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.Now.instant \- Temporal.Now.instant()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Temporal.Now.instant()\f[B]\f[R] static method returns
the current time as a \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
Temporal.Now.instant()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
A \f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R] object representing the current time, with
potentially reduced precision.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Measuring time elapsed
The following example measures two instants in time and calculates the
duration between them, and gets the total duration in milliseconds:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] start = Temporal.Now.instant();
\f[I]// Do something that takes time\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] end = Temporal.Now.instant();
\f[B]const\f[R] duration = end.since(start);
console.log(duration.total(\(dqmilliseconds\(dq));
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.Now\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.Instant\f[R]
